item.dc:creator: @arham_4 arham 4
item.description:
@arham_4 wrote:

[quote=“Merlen321, post:3, topic:387167”]This happened to me also. It is VERY easy to fix. start>computer>C:>Program Files>Java

You should see a application file. Mine is 6u24. (Yours might not be 24). If you dont have it, you need to download JDK6, just google it. Now open up whatever you need. Look for the “JDK1.6.0_**” say it is JDK1.6.0_21 and you have 24, it will read JDK1.6.0_24 then[/quote]
Exactly what I told him

item.title: Need urgent help
item.dc:creator: @arham_4 arham 4
item.description:
@arham_4 wrote:

right click and press edit. Then, you will see:

jdk1.6.0_##

assuming there are 2 numbers in ##. Change the ## into your java version. To figure out, go to C; drive and press program files. Press java and you will see jdk1.6.0_## (the ## are your java version). So, if you were to have the laest version the ## would be 24. Change the ## in the compiler to 24.
